cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  This repository (fhir-mcp-eval) is an experimental harness adapted from
  FHIR-AgentBench. If you use it, please cite the original FHIR-AgentBench paper
  (the "preferred-citation" below), which is the benchmark and dataset this work
  builds on.
title: "fhir-mcp-eval: does adding MCP tools make an LLM agent more accurate? An honest FHIR/Medplum agent eval"
abstract: >-
  An experimental harness for measuring whether exposing tools to an LLM agent
  through an MCP server actually improves accuracy, worked through a FHIR / Medplum
  clinical-QA case study on the open-access MIMIC-IV-on-FHIR demo. Adapted from
  glee4810/FHIR-AgentBench (CC BY 4.0).
type: software
authors:
  - name: CoralEHR
repository-code: "https://github.com/coralehr/fhir-mcp-eval"
license: CC-BY-4.0
keywords:
  - FHIR
  - MCP
  - LLM agents
  - clinical question answering
  - evaluation
  - Medplum
preferred-citation:
  type: conference-paper
  title: "FHIR-AgentBench: Benchmarking LLM Agents for Realistic Interoperable EHR Question Answering"
  year: 2025
